message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: LLM Network Latency Measurement Experiment on Digital Front-End Test Platforms
abstract: This dataset comprises results from an experiment designed to measure network
  latency using a load generation application within a controlled environment. The
  methodology involved establishing a DUT and load generator configuration across
  nodes nida and cesis, utilizing Git repositories for software libraries and applications.
  Per-run logs captured energy consumption and generated latency histograms, evaluating
  performance under configurable packet rates and sizes. Synchronization mechanisms
  ensured consistent execution across multiple iterations of the load generation and
  L2 forwarder experiments, ultimately providing data for analyzing network behavior
  characteristics.
